data.description: 40 beautiful acres and a Designer's own home with lots of fun artsy detail. On the market for the first time, this sweet home has a fairy tale feel and lives larger than the sqft. Originally designed to be the guest house, the property is all set up for a second home, with a 4-bedroom septic, water holding tanks, 5.34 KW solar system and 440-amp electrical service - on 40 acres you could create a family compound with multiple view building sites to choose from. There are paths to hike, a charming gravel patio area with tree rounds for stepping stones, a picnic area and a large garden area. 2x6 construction, 2 tone stucco and standing seam metal roof make this home fire resilient, the upgraded plentiful, dual pane windows and huge skylight in the apex bring light and nature into this open floorplan. The 2-car garage was intended up to use as an office on one half. The barn consists of two 12 x 12 stalls and a 10 x 12 tack/feed room. Plans come with the property if desired. Just a few miles to schools, shopping, services and dining. Assumable VA Loan! Possibilities include splitting, Ranching, vineyard and more.
